article.headline: Wis.-Milwaukee 60, Cleveland St. 48
article.story: CLEVELAND (AP) -- Allan Hanson scored 15 points and Avery Smith added 12, including a layup that put Wisconsin-Milwaukee up for good, as the Panthers beat Cleveland State 60-48 Thursday night. Marcus Skinner added 10 points for Wisconsin-Milwaukee (5-13, 2-3 Horizon League). He, Hanson, and Smith had six rebounds apiece. Carlos English led the Vikings (6-12, 0-5) with 12 points, including a game-high five 3-pointers. J'Nathan Bullock added 11 points and a game-high nine rebounds, and Patrick Tatham added eight rebounds. Cleveland State outshot Wisconsin-Milwaukee from the floor in the first half about 39 percent (11-of-28) to 30 percent (9-of-30) to pull ahead 28-24 at the break. But Wisconsin-Milwaukee outshot the Vikings in the second half about 67 percent (12-of-18) to 24 percent (7-of-29) on field goals. Cleveland State pulled to an 8-point lead, its highest of the game, in the first minute of the second half and held the lead for most of the next 10 minutes. But Wisconsin-Milwaukee pulled ahead for good on Smith's layup with 7:34 left to play. The Panthers' largest lead came at the end of the game.
